  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of life-saving WASH, Child Protection and Nutrition services for the flood affected
people in Bangladesh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to ensure people are able to meet basic food and other essential needs following the floods. This UNICEF project provides 1) 250,000 people with sufficient/safe water for drinking/cooking/hygiene, 2) 1,200 household sanitation facilitities and/or bathing facilities, 3) 13,000 with mental health and/or psycho-social support services, 4) 3,000 in-kind NFI kits and 5) 3,400 children with severe acute manlnutrition treatment among other activities. The project provides life-saving assistance to 250,000 people, including 83,520 women, 80,244 men, 86,000 children, and 3,580 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
